<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Courses</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.1/css/bootstrap.min.css">
	<script src="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.1/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
	<div class="jumbotron">
    <form action="/search" method="post" class="navbar-form navbar-right">
			<div class="form-group">
				<input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Search">
			</div>
			<button type="submit" class="btn btn-default">Submit</button>
		</form>
		<h1>My Courser</h1>
		<h3>It's gotten easier to be the best student you can be. </h3>
		<p>Courser is a personal tool to help you keep track of your courses and school schedule.<br> 
		Monitor your progress and improvement over time to achieve your goals.</p>

		<b>Here's an example.</b> <%= @example_courses %>
		
		<hr style="color:#919090; background-color:#919090; height:1px; border:none;">

		<h4><p style="line-height:1.5">
			<% @courses.each do |course| %> <!-- refers to item in collection or block (table and class). class corresponds to table.class is capital and refers to concept of school). item = instance, record. schools refers to collection -->
			<span class="label label-primary"><%= course.term %></span> &nbsp;&nbsp;<%= course.name %> - <%= course.professor_name %>&nbsp;<%= course.time1 %> - <a href="/courses/<%= course.id %>/edit">Edit</a><br>
			<% end %>
		</p></h4>

		<br>
		<br>	
		<a href="/courses/new"><button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg btn-block">Add A New Course</button></a>
		<br>		

	</div>
</body>
</html>